description:
You will develop a Territory in constant evolution, driven by the natural interactions between the species that inhabit it.

On their turn, a player:

places one of their two selected tiles orthogonally adjacent to a tile already in the Territory;
applies the effect of the placed tile by flipping the targeted tiles;
selects a new tile from their reserve to once again have two tiles available for their next turn.

When each player has only one tile left in front of them, everyone adds up the values of the 6 tiles they played onto the Territory, then adds the bonus points from their unplayed tile:

the front-side points if there are at least 4 tiles of their color showing the front side;
the back-side points if there are at least 4 tiles of their color showing the back side;
no points if there are 3 front-side tiles and 3 back-side tiles.

The player with the highest score wins the game! of surprises!

KABAHHN is a game where players work together to arrange the fruit cards dealt to each player in ascending order of size!
But the only way to communicate size is by opening your mouth! Open your mouths on the signal: &ldquo;Ready&hellip;KABAHHN!&rdquo;

&mdash;description from the publisher

In a distant galaxy, natural resources are running out and advanced civilizations send travelers through space in search of their most valuable fuel: milk! What a surprise these aliens had when they arrived on Earth and found, in abundance, the source of this precious material. Now they must bring this treasure back to their planets, no matter the cost.


     Throw the ball at the cows to capture them;
     Avoid the barn and the farmer;
     Be the first to fill your spaceship with five cows to win the game;


A fun dexterity game where players compete as aliens trying to abduct cows using skill and precision.

Your Worst Night Out is a cooperative game where all participants are part of the same team. The goal is to accumulate as many points as possible by guessing the worst and least worst nights out of the other players.

&bull;&bull;&bull;

Ta Pire Soir&eacute;e est un jeu collaboratif o&ugrave; tous les participants font partie d&rsquo;une m&ecirc;me &eacute;quipe. Le but est d&rsquo;accumuler le plus de points possible en devinant quelles seraient les pires et les moins pires soir&eacute;es des autres joueurs.

A big box that has room for the base game and contains:
 - Misfit Healers expansion (adds the new healing ability which adds even more combos to the game);
 - 120 Printed Card Sleeves;
 - 100 Wood Coins;
 - 24 Wooden Quest tiles;
 - 72 Wooden influence tokens;
 - 1 Wooden First Player marker;
 - 4 Player Mats.

Heart of Nile (尼罗之心) is a competitive set-collection board game for 3&ndash;5 players set in ancient Egypt. Players take on the roles of gem collectors seeking prestige by climbing towers, visiting merchant guilds, and dealing with shadowy figures in the black market. Through clever choices and timing, they compete to earn the prestigious title of the &ldquo;Heart of the Nile.&rdquo;

&mdash;description from the publisher

This game is part of the third edition of the 9 Cards series.

&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve had my fill of smoked fish&rdquo;, the alderman of the little Dutch town grumbles. &ldquo;Bring me some apples to finish the meal!&rdquo;. His servant looks worried. &ldquo;We are out of apples sir. The De Witt family has been cutting peat close to our lands and now the water level in our orchards is too high.&rdquo; The alderman&rsquo;s face turns into a frown: &ldquo;I will go to the count of Holland and file a complaint. The count will surely be on my side.&rdquo; The servant bows and takes his leave. He knows the count has just delegated all water related decisions to a new court close by. The judge presiding is married to De Witt&rsquo;s sister&hellip;

Bailiff of Boscoop is a strategy game set in the late Middle Ages and Early Modern period in Rhineland, part of the county of Holland in what is now The Netherlands. 2-5 players take on the role of local families. Players perform actions in sequence. Family members may claim land. Some may rise to prominence as the founder of a village, as a judge, or as a local duck dealer. The family with the most land at the end of the game wins.

&mdash;description from the publisher
